File_Description: "10,368" corrected measurements of potential activity of the exoenzymes beta-glucosidase; leucine/leucyl aminopeptidase; and acid phosphatase in 18 soil samples collected from six depths in each of three replicate soil cores after incubation with each of eight substrate concentrations and under each of six temperatures. Values include quadruplicate measurements under each combination of conditions.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure 1.0.0
ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure 1.0.0

File_Description: 313 corrected values of each of five Michaelis-Menten kinetic parameters of the exoenzymes beta-glucosidase; leucine/leucyl aminopeptidase; and acid phosphatase in 18 soil samples collected from six depths in each of three replicate soil cores; after incubation under each of six temperatures. Michaelis-Menten kinetics were modeled over quadruplicate measurements of enzyme activity under each of the cominations of conditions. Individual enzyme acivity measurements ar available in file "enzymeActivity_corr.csv". Parameters: maximum reaction velocity (Vmax; on dry soil and microbial biomass C basis); half-saturation/Michaelis constant (Km); and catalytic efficiency (CE; on dry soil and microbial biomass C basis).
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure 1.0.0

File_Description: 108 mean values and respective standard deviations and standard errors; of each of five Michaelis-Menten kinetic parameters of the exoenzymes beta-glucosidase; leucine/leucyl aminopeptidase; and acid phosphatase in triplicate soil samples collected from each of six soil depths; after incubation under each of six temperatures. Individual replicate values are available in file "enzymeKinetics_corr.csv". Michaelis-Menten kinetics were modeled over quadruplicate measurements of enzyme activity under each of the cominations of conditions (file "enzymeActivity_corr.csv"). Parameters: maximum reaction velocity (Vmax; on dry soil and microbial biomass C basis); half-saturation/Michaelis constant (Km); and catalytic efficiency (CE; on dry soil and microbial biomass C basis).
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure 1.0.0

File_Description: CSV data dictionary for files "enzymeKinetics_corr.csv" and "enzymeKinetics_corr_means.csv"
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure 1.0.0

File_Description: 54 corrected values of each of multiple temperature sensitivity parameters of the exoenzymes beta-glucosidase; leucine/leucyl aminopeptidase; and acid phosphatase in 18 soil samples collected from six depths in each of three replicate soil cores. Parameters: activation energy and Q10 indices of Vmax; Km; and catalytic efficiency (linear Arrhenius model); temperature optimum; point of maximum temperature sensitivity; and change in heat capacity (non-linear Macromolecular Rate Theory model). Arrhenius parameters and Q10 were modeled over five temperatures between 4-35 degree Celsius and six temperatures between 4-50 degree Celsius; Macromolecular Rate Theory parameters were modeled over only six temperatures between 4-50 degree Celsius.
Standard: ESS-DIVE Reporting Format for Comma-separated Values (CSV) File Structure 1.0.0

Parameters: activation energy and Q10 indices of Vmax; Km; and catalytic efficiency (linear Arrhenius model); temperature optimum; point of maximum temperature sensitivity; and change in heat capacity (non-linear Macromolecular Rate Theory model).
